{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c3d12422-3a07-43a2-b9cc-e36b57e4a29b","content":".NET is available but `dotnet-dump` isn't installed yet. Here's what to do:\n\n### 1. Install `dotnet-dump`\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n```\n\n### 2. Analyze your dump\n```bash\ndotnet-dump analyze /path/to/your-file.dmp\n```\n\n### 3. Useful commands inside the analyzer\n\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `pe` (PrintException) | Show the last exception |\n| `clrthreads` | List all managed threads |\n| `setthread <id>` | Switch to a thread |\n| `dso` (DumpStackObjects) | Objects on the stack |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap overview |\n| `exit` | Quit |\n\n### Typical crash investigation flow:\n1. Run `pe` to check if there's an unhandled exception\n2. Run `clrthreads` to find threads with exceptions\n3. Use `setthread` + `clrstack` to inspect each thread's stack\n4. Use `dso` to inspect objects involved\n\n**Would you like me to install `dotnet-dump` and start an interactive analysis session with your dump file?** If so, let me know the path to your `.dmp` file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fade39b2-ef44-4bff-b00d-1733f04ef12c","outputTokens":323,"requestId":"DA01:1287AC:7238546:7AED402:6A03DA26"},"id":"8b1035ab-990b-4cc1-a04f-b8a78c6df8fc","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:56:03.139Z","parentId":"ea6312b8-9a2c-4a51-ba0f-884087359e9c"}
